tr: the act of competing as for profit or a prize
example: the teams were in fierce contention for first place

tr: an occasion on which a winner is selected from among two or more contestants
the contestant you hope to defeat
example: he had respect for his rivals
he wanted to know what the competition was doing

tr: a business relation in which two parties compete to gain customers
example: business competition can be fiendish at times

data.enText: a situation in which people or organizations compete with each other for sth that not everyone can have
There is now intense competition between schools to attract students.
data.chText: 现在学校之间为了招揽生源展开了激烈竞争。

data.enText: We are in competition with four other companies for the contract.
data.chText: 我们在与其他四家公司竞争这项合同。

data.enText: We won the contract in the face of stiff competition .
data.chText: 面对激烈的竞争，我们赢得了这项合同。

data.enText: an event in which people compete with each other to find out who is the best at sth

data.chText: 参加 / 赢得 / 输掉比赛

data.enText: the people who are competing against sb

data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的单数名词

data.enText: We'll be able to assess the competition at the conference.
data.chText: 我们可以在会上对竞争对手进行估量。

ex.enText: There is a tennis match tomorrow.
How many matches are there this season?

synonyms.bx: 通常指体育比赛，一般在两人或两队之间进行。

ex.enText: He was the winner of that photography competition.
ex.chText: 他是那次摄影比赛的优胜者。

synonyms.bx: 指体育比赛或知识、技巧等方面的比赛。

ex.enText: The spelling contest will take place at our school next week.
ex.chText: 拼写比赛下周将在我们学校举行。

ex.enText: Are you going to attend the talent contest?
ex.chText: 你将参加新秀选拔赛吗？

synonyms.bx: 尤指某种技能活动或体育运动的比赛。

ex.enText: She prefers to see games on TV with her family.
ex.chText: 她更喜欢和家人一起看电视转播的比赛。

ex.enText: What's the result of the Spain's World Cup game against France?
ex.chText: 西班牙队对阵法国队的那场世界杯比赛结果如何？

synonyms.bx: 泛指有一定规则的比赛，如游戏、体育运动等。

example.ex: There's been some fierce competition for the title...
example.tran: 夺冠之争一直都相当激烈。

example.ex: It was in these studios that young painters found the support and stimulating competition of peers.
example.tran: 就是在这些画室里，年轻的画家们得到了同龄人的支持，也感受到了激励大家向前的竞争。

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft adj N, N prep

value.def: Competition is a situation in which two or more people or groups are trying to get something which not everyone can have.

example.ex: I have to change my approach, the competition is too good now.
example.tran: 我得改变方法，现在的竞争对手太强。

value.def: The competition is the person or people you are competing with.

example.ex: The deal would have reduced competition in the commuter-aircraft market...
example.tran: 这项协议原本会减少通勤航班市场的竞争。

example.ex: The farmers have been seeking higher prices as better protection from foreign competition...
example.tran: 农场主们一直在寻找更高的价格，以更好地保护自己不受国外竞争对手的影响。

example.ex: Clothing stores also face heavy competition from factory outlets.
example.tran: 成衣店也面临着来自工厂直销店的激烈竞争。

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft adj N, N prep

value.def: Competition is an activity involving two or more firms, in which each firm tries to get people to buy its own goods in preference to the other firms' goods.

example.ex: The American aerospace industry has been challenged by some stiff competition.
example.tran: 美国航空和航天工业已经受到某种强劲的竞争产品的挑战。

value.def: The competition is the goods that a rival organization is selling.

example.ex: The council has organised a series of events and competitions for school children in the area...
example.tran: 委员会为本地区的中小学生组织了一系列的活动和比赛。

example.ex: He will be banned from international competition for four years.
example.tran: 他将被禁赛4年，禁赛期间不能参加任何国际比赛。

value.def: A competition is an event in which many people take part in order to find out who is best at a particular activity.
